text: <@U3HS0S61K> please feel free to file issues at <https://jira.hyperledger.org>, use “Component=fabric-sdk-node"
<@U13TWBRBL> ok, but how to sign up there? I have LFID but jira requires some login/password...
<@U3HS0S61K> - your LFID and password should work
<@U0PB67X4K> my LFID is w/o password, via OAuth
ah - well don't know how to help with that one.  I assume you had a password at some point?  :wink:
(Good morning) <@U3HS0S61K>, wanna to give <https://identity.linuxfoundation.org> a try ?
I think you can request a new password, and/or log on with a different provider.

<@U3HS0S61K> ok this is now coming back to me, I also first requested a LFID using oauth, and of course it won’t work with jira which only supports basic auth. I had to request a new ID without using any of the oauth providers. so I have two LFIDs now
<@U11MANG9G> <@U13TWBRBL> ok, I reset "forgotten" password and logged in successfully, thanks!
Thanks <@U13TWBRBL> New SDK Video posted on youtube, including how build outside of vagrant! <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t7PcpkIoGAc>

text: <@U13TWBRBL> Thank you for a new SDK Video! The error shown in the Video will be resolved by this patch. <https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/#/c/3569/>
<@U1GRJD9NC>: thanks for proposing the fix, I'll review it later tonight

Please note that at around 15:06 the screenshot showed that the resulting block from “step2” has [0] transactions, meaning the failure from VSCC is actually valid (despite what I said in the video). This is due to a bug that will be fixed by <@U2231CUH3>  in <https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/#/c/3569>
